definitions.definition: To end something, especially when left in an incomplete state.
examples: to terminate a process before its completion
to terminate an effort, or a controversy

definitions.definition: To set or be a limit or boundary to.
examples: to terminate a surface by a line

definitions.definition: To form an appropriate end on (a wire, cable, hose, pipe, etc), such as by applying a cable terminal or a hose ferrule .
examples: We'll rough them all in before we start terminating any of them.

definitions.definition: To end the employment contract of an employee; to fire , lay off .

examples: The enemy must be terminated by any means possible.

definitions.definition: To end , conclude , or cease ; to come to an end .
Of a mode of transport, to end its journey; or, of a railway line, to reach its terminus .
examples: This train terminates at the next station.

main_definition: ( transitive ) To end something, especially when left in an incomplete state.
secondary_definitions: ( transitive ) To set or be a limit or boundary to.
( transitive ) To form an appropriate end on (a wire, cable, hose, pipe, etc), such as by applying a cable terminal or a hose ferrule .
( transitive ) To end the employment contract of an employee; to fire , lay off .
( transitive , euphemistic ) To kill someone or something.
( intransitive ) To end , conclude , or cease ; to come to an end .
( intransitive ) Of a mode of transport, to end its journey; or, of a railway line, to reach its terminus .
